{/* Hero / Intro */}

About Us

GalaxyEDGE Safety Inc.

At GalaxyEDGE Safety Inc. (GESI), we are redefining global health and safety standards through innovation, digital transformation, and immersive learning technologies. Our mission is to lead the industry by integrating AI-powered safety solutions, cutting-edge digital tools, and accessible training programs to create safer, smarter workplaces worldwide.

{/* Mission / Vision / Values */}

Lisa McGuire, ICD.D, CRSP

A Transformational Leader in Workplace Safety

Lisa McGuire, ICD.D, CRSP, is a recognized leader in occupational health and safety, with over 17 years of executive experience driving industry transformation, digital innovation, and global standardization. As a visionary entrepreneur and corporate director, she has founded and led multiple organizations dedicated to advancing safety excellence, leadership engagement, and workforce education through technology and strategic governance. As Founder & CEO of the Manufacturing Safety Alliance of BC (MSABC), Lisa spearheaded an industry- wide movement that resulted in a 40% reduction in injury rates within the food subsector and expanded the organization’s reach from 800 to 3,000 member businesses. She also led the creation of Safety Meta World, a groundbreaking subsidiary that introduced immersive, game-based safety training solutions, enhancing training effectiveness by 60% and revolutionizing safety education accessibility worldwide. Lisa played a pivotal role in the development of Canada’s first harmonized OHS practitioner competency and capability standard in manufacturing, an eight-year initiative funded by the BC Ministry of Post-Secondary Education and Future Skills. This framework established a structured, validated competency model aligned with IOSH and INSHPO global standards, integrating business acumen, cybersecurity, data-driven decision-making, psychological health, and leadership skills into professional OHS practice. Her work has laid the foundation for consistent, high-quality occupational health and safety practices across Canada and beyond. Recognizing that effective safety leadership starts at the executive level, Lisa founded the Executive Health & Safety Council of BC (EHSCBC) to cultivate a culture of proactive leadership, shared responsibility, and corporate governance in workplace health and safety. Lisa continues to drive innovation in digital safety solutions and is currently partnering with an award- winning digital technology firm to develop an AI-powered OHS Assistant, a pioneering initiative that will leverage artificial intelligence to positively impact and enhance workplace health and safety performance globally—with more details to be announced soon. As an ICD.D accredited corporate director, Lisa has shaped industry governance, regulatory standards, and occupational health and safety frameworks at both the national and international levels. Her leadership continues to influence the future of workplace safety, ensuring that organizations are equipped with the most advanced tools, strategies, and governance models to drive safer, more sustainable workplaces worldwide.
